Subject: [PATCH AP-05] vmnet: add VMW_NETIF_SINGLE_NAPI_PARM detection to Makefile.kernel

compat_netdevice.h uses the compile-time flag VMW_NETIF_SINGLE_NAPI_PARM to
select the correct netif_napi_add variant for kernel >= 6.1. This flag is
set via vm_check_build in Makefile.normal but is NOT set in Makefile.kernel,
meaning it is never active under the kbuild system.

This patch adds the vm_check_build call for a synthetic probe file
(netif_napi_add_check.c) that tests whether the kernel's netif_napi_add
accepts 3 arguments. If the probe compiles successfully, -DVMW_NETIF_SINGLE_NAPI_PARM
is added to ccflags-y, enabling the correct 3-arg path in compat_netdevice.h.

The probe file (netif_napi_add_check.c) is created alongside this patch by the
script. It attempts to call the 3-arg form; if the kernel has it, the probe
compiles and the flag is set.

Source note: VMware Workstation Pro 25H2u1 vmnet-only/Makefile.kernel uses
'ccflags-y +=' (not ':=') for the final ccflags-y line. This patch targets
25H2u1 sources. For the 6.16.x community overlay the anchor is 'ccflags-y :='
instead, but the injected line is identical.

Applied by: _autopatch_vmnet_napi_flag() in vmware_module_builder.py
Condition:  kernel >= 6.1 AND VMW_NETIF_SINGLE_NAPI_PARM not already set

---
 vmnet-only/Makefile.kernel         | 4 ++++
 vmnet-only/netif_napi_add_check.c  | 6 ++++++
 2 files changed, 10 insertions(+)

diff --git a/vmnet-only/Makefile.kernel b/vmnet-only/Makefile.kernel
--- a/vmnet-only/Makefile.kernel
+++ b/vmnet-only/Makefile.kernel
@@ -23,6 +23,10 @@ EXTRA_CFLAGS := $(CC_OPTS) $(INCLUDE) $(VMW_CFLAGS)
 ccflags-y += $(EXTRA_CFLAGS)
 
+# Detect 3-arg netif_napi_add (kernel 6.1+ dropped the weight param)
+ccflags-y += $(call vm_check_build, $(SRCROOT)/netif_napi_add_check.c,-DVMW_NETIF_SINGLE_NAPI_PARM, )
+
 obj-m += $(DRIVER).o

diff --git a/vmnet-only/netif_napi_add_check.c b/vmnet-only/netif_napi_add_check.c
new file mode 100644
--- /dev/null
+++ b/vmnet-only/netif_napi_add_check.c
@@ -0,0 +1,6 @@
+/* autopatch probe: detect 3-arg netif_napi_add (kernel 6.1+) */
+#include <linux/netdevice.h>
+static int dummy_poll(struct napi_struct *n, int b) { return 0; }
+void test(struct net_device *dev, struct napi_struct *napi) {
+    netif_napi_add(dev, napi, dummy_poll);
+}
